      %h4 Privacy Policy - Last Updated 6/24/14
      %p This policy details how data about you is collected/used/disclosed when you visit our websites and services (together, "Fauna") or otherwise interact with us. If we update it, we will revise the date, place notices on Fauna if a change is material, and/or obtain your consent as required by law.
      %p We take precautions to prevent unauthorized access to or misuse of data about you.  We do not share your data with third parties for marketing purposes that have not been vetted by our staff and deemed safe and reputable.  Data we use to provide/improve our services and/or combat fraud/abuse includes an data you post on Fauna, log data obtained via anonymous tracking services, data collected via cookies, data about the your devices, and data from 3rd parties.  We retain data as long as needed for our business purposes and/or as required by law.  We make good faith efforts to store data securely, but make no guarantees.  You may access and update certain data about you by logging into your account.  
      %p We may disclose user data to vendors, sellers, buyers, and service providers (e.g. payment processors) working on our behalf.  We also may disclose data under other circumstances including to respond to subpoenas, court orders, or other legal process, to protect our rights, property, or safety, or that of our users or the general public, with your consent, in connection with a merger, bankruptcy, or sale/transfer of assets to another company, and in aggregate or summary form, as long as it cannot reasonably be used to identify you.
      %p International Users - By visiting Fauna or providing us data, you agree we may use and disclose data we collect for purposes listed here or as communicated to you, transmit it outside your resident jurisdiction, and store it on servers in the United States. For more information please contact our privacy officer at support@fauna.net.
